title: The Collected Stuff of Legend (2009-2012) (Digital) (Empire)
description:
This is an "all-ages" comic in the true sense of the term: The plot (a band of anthropomorphic toys goes on a quest to rescue "their child" from a monster-under-the-bed-type villain) will certainly appeal to children, but turns out to be remarkably dark, deep, and intricate, and the sepia artwork is some of the most gorgeous I've ever seen. Details: <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Stuff_of_Legend" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Stuff_of_Legend</a>

Contains:

VOLUME I: THE DARK - The original 2009/10 instalment. Two oversized issues (100+ pages total), compiled into one pseudo-TPB from Digital Mid-Res releases by Empire.

VOLUME II: THE JUNGLE - 2010/11. Four normal-sized issues compiled into one from Digital Mid-Res releases by Empire.

VOLUME III: A JESTER'S TALE - 2011/12. Ditto.

VOLUME IV: THE TOY COLLECTOR - 2012/13. Five issues compiled into one from Digital High-Res to Very-High-Res (with double-width pages weighing in at a whopping 5,120 x 2,560 pixels, doing the illustrations the justice they deserve) releases by Empire.

Excludes:

There have been FCBD issues published every year since the series' inception. I managed to track down all of them except for this year's, but kept none, as each turned out to be nothing more than a preview for the at-the-time upcoming volume.
